&lt;p&gt;Permanent/Fixed term&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service is for people over 18 who live in or are registered with a GP in Trafford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patients may present with concerns around swallowing function (Dysphagia) and /or communication difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These difficulties may arise as a result of varied diagnoses including Stroke, Dementia, Progressive Neurological Conditions, Respiratory Disease and Head and Neck Cancers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patients can self-refer for communication problems but a medical referral is required for dysphagia, either from GP, consultant or SLT colleague transfer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides assessment, diagnosis and management of these disorders in the community setting. This includes clinic appointments, visits to own home, and nursing or residential care homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education, training and support are an important aspect of our intervention alongside direct therapy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
